{"id": 6430, "title": "Ticket #6430: docker universe should report RSS of container in MemoryUsage", "description": "<blockquote>\nCurrently, docker reports memory usage by polling the max_usage field from the container.  In newer versions of docker, this is the sum of memory allocated by the container + the file system cache.  There is another field, rss which is just the rss reported by the container.  Docker should use that field instead.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Oct-25 16:37:50 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Doc review:</strong> OK</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-24 17:41</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/fa155f24f06abda1e3fd050d855a72e0f97b0332\">[52648]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6430\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6430'); return false;\" title=\"docker universe should report RSS of container in MemoryUsage\">#6430</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-04 15:16</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5af1b5919e70b43805ea8f7bbc142b83869ac4ff\">[52482]</a></span>: Have docker report <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=MemoryUsage\" title=\"Memory Usage\">MemoryUsage</a></span> as rss, not rss + cache <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6430\" onclick=\"get_